    "body": "### Problem\n\ncan't use `nvim_get_mode` inside `InsertEnter` autocmd callback\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. prepare file `minimal.lua`\n\n```\nvim.opt.showmode = false\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({'InsertEnter'}, {callback = function() vim.print(vim.api.nvim_get_mode().mode) end})\n```\n\n2. run `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\n\n3. press `i` to enter insert mode\n\n4. prompt `n`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nprompt `i`\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1287+g8f84167c30\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot sure\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n6.12.1-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst 0.8.5\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nrelease page",
